  "prompt": "My interview in IOCL lasted for 30 minutes but the interview was below average.What are my chances of getting selected?",
  "response": "It's difficult to assess your chances of being selected based on the length of the interview and your perception of its quality. Several factors can influence the decision, including:\n\n1. **Interview Performance**: If you feel that your responses were not strong, it's possible it may affect your chances, but interviewers consider various aspects of a candidate's potential.\n\n2. **Number of Candidates**: The competitiveness of the applicant pool also plays a significant role. If many strong candidates were interviewed, it could be more challenging.\n\n3. **Interview Structure**: Some interviews may be shorter or less formal, and that doesn't necessarily mean a candidate has been ruled out. Interviewers sometimes use concise assessments.\n\n4. **Overall Application**: Your qualifications, experience, and other application materials might still make you a strong candidate, even if the interview was not ideal.\n\n5. **Feedback and Follow-up**: Sometimes, companies provide feedback or follow-up opportunities that can give you more information about your standing.\n\nWhile it's natural to feel uncertain after an interview, it's best to stay positive and consider preparing for other opportunities as well. Good luck!",
